) largely covered with pale, fine setae, decreasing in length towards apex, basal ones longer and sinuous (
<collectionCode box="[889,970,1394,1418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">MSSC</collectionCode>
); base of FI (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1180,1394,1418]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[263,1333,733,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[243,1350,720,1960]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male. 1, habitus. 2, fore coxa and femur (permanent slide). 3, fore tarsus (permanent slide). 4, mid femur and tibia (permanent slide). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[1165,1180,1394,1418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number box="[1251,1265,1394,1418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
pale, long posteroventral setae, and with anterior bush-like comb of brown setae (
<collectionCode box="[927,1008,1430,1454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">MSSC</collectionCode>
); tibia I covered by fine setae, longer dorsally; tarsus I (
<figureCitation box="[351,417,1466,1490]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[263,1333,733,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[243,1350,720,1960]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male. 1, habitus. 2, fore coxa and femur (permanent slide). 3, fore tarsus (permanent slide). 4, mid femur and tibia (permanent slide). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[403,417,1466,1490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with ventral surface entirely bare, dorsal surface covered by pale setae; tarsomere 
<number box="[1344,1358,1466,1490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
longer than sum of remaining tarsomeres, ventrally swollen at basal 
<number box="[852,862,1502,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[873,887,1502,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
(all 
<collectionCode box="[942,1021,1502,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">MSSC</collectionCode>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1041,1126,1502,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Leg II:</emphasis>
CxII with few pale setulae anteriorly, bare laterally; FII (
<figureCitation box="[489,558,1538,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[263,1333,733,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[243,1350,720,1960]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male. 1, habitus. 2, fore coxa and femur (permanent slide). 3, fore tarsus (permanent slide). 4, mid femur and tibia (permanent slide). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[543,558,1538,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) with anterodorsal row of strong brown setae along apical 
<number box="[1234,1249,1538,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1259,1272,1538,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
, decreasing in length towards apex, ventral surface completely bare, except for anteroventral row of pale setae along basal 
<number box="[1393,1406,1574,1598]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1416,1431,1574,1598]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="4.0">4</number>
, decreasing in length towards apex, and 
<number box="[596,610,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
sinuous, brown anteroventral seta (all 
<collectionCode box="[1048,1127,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">MSSC</collectionCode>
); tibia II (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1307,1610,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[263,1333,733,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[243,1350,720,1960]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male. 1, habitus. 2, fore coxa and femur (permanent slide). 3, fore tarsus (permanent slide). 4, mid femur and tibia (permanent slide). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201977/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[1292,1307,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) with anterior row of brown setae, strongly curved medially (
<collectionCode box="[725,805,1646,1670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">MSSC</collectionCode>
), 
<number box="[824,838,1646,1670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
small, brown ventral apical seta. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1216,1310,1646,1670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Leg III:</emphasis>
CxIII with conspicuous, long, pale seta near base, and 
<number box="[642,656,1682,1706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
pale setulae anteriad; 
<collectionCode box="[909,953,1683,1706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">FIII</collectionCode>
with dorsal row of black setae, decreasing in length towards apex; tibia III with 
<number box="[580,594,1718,1742]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
dorsal brown seta at distal 
<number box="[911,921,1718,1742]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[932,949,1718,1742]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="4.0">4</number>
, and comb of pale ventral setulae apically, upper to tarsal excavation (
<collectionCode box="[458,539,1754,1778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">MSSC</collectionCode>
); IIIt 
<number box="[595,603,1769,1783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
with ventral excavation at base (
<collectionCode box="[978,1059,1754,1778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">MSSC</collectionCode>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1078,1204,1754,1779]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Mostly brown, with some dark blue reflections on T 
<number box="[509,553,1793,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
. T 
<number box="[583,623,1793,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
covered by short black setae. Segment 
<number box="[1067,1081,1793,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="6.0">6</number>
hidden under T 
<number box="[1262,1276,1793,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="5.0">5</number>
, T 
<number box="[1305,1318,1793,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="6.0">6</number>
bare; segment 
<number box="[216,230,1830,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="7.0">7</number>
forming short peduncle, T 
<number box="[538,551,1830,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="7.0">7</number>
and S 
<number box="[625,639,1829,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="7.0">7</number>
bare; S 
<number box="[729,743,1829,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="8.0">8</number>
small, triangular. S 
<number box="[967,1009,1829,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
visible, sclerotized, S 
<number box="[1260,1275,1829,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="4.0">4</number>
membranous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1864,1889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[323,434,1865,1889]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[250,1335,204,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[219,1364,193,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male hypopygium. 5, left lateral view. 6, right lateral view, but reflected (right cercus removed). 7, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm. See Material and methods for explanation of abbreviations." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201978/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
Figs. 
<number box="[387,434,1865,1889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
</figureCitation>
): Epandrium elongate, twice longer than high, dark. Epandrial lobe elongate, digitiform, with 
<number box="[211,225,1901,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
small dorsal setae at apex. DSur and VSur enlarged, placoid, covering internal appendages and phallushypandrium; VSur twice higher than DSur, with 
<number box="[714,728,1937,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
internal setae at apex. Pair of hook-like lateral projections of VSur ending at mesal, sharp unpaired sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[677,746,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[250,1335,204,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[219,1364,193,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male hypopygium. 5, left lateral view. 6, right lateral view, but reflected (right cercus removed). 7, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm. See Material and methods for explanation of abbreviations." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201978/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[730,746,1973,1997]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium basally fused to epandrium. Phallus with short dorsal projection near apex. Cercus rounded and covered by fine setae, with digitiform projection apically with spine (
<figureCitation box="[225,293,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[250,1335,204,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[219,1364,193,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male hypopygium. 5, left lateral view. 6, right lateral view, but reflected (right cercus removed). 7, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm. See Material and methods for explanation of abbreviations." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201978/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[276,293,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pair of internal appendages next to cercus bearing curved seta at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1169,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[250,1335,204,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[219,1364,193,1913]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: male hypopygium. 5, left lateral view. 6, right lateral view, but reflected (right cercus removed). 7, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm. See Material and methods for explanation of abbreviations." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201978/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[1152,1169,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1188,1284,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">Female:</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[151,290,188,212]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.0999999999999996" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.9">2.9–3.3 mm</quantity>
. Wing: 
<quantity box="[380,516,188,212]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.9 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[589,726,188,212]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.1 mm</quantity>
wide. Habitus similar to male, except by 
<collectionCode box="[1203,1278,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">MSSC</collectionCode>
and as noted. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,224,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">Head:</emphasis>
Face slightly broader than in males (about as broad as ocellar tubercle), slightly wider towards apex, clypeal suture evident; first flagellomere shorter. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[628,693,259,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[712,797,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[309,1278,1129,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[289,1298,1097,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 11. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: wings (permanent slide). 10, male. 11, female. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. See Material and methods for explanation of abbreviations." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201980/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[767,797,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
): Spurious veins on R 
<number box="[1056,1064,275,289]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1073,1080,275,289]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="5.0">5</number>
and M much shorter, fewer in number and restricted to distal parts of veins than in males, no spurious veins on dm-cu; R 
<number box="[1153,1161,314,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1170,1177,314,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="5.0">5</number>
and M converging distally, M ending at apex; R 
<number box="[443,451,352,366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[459,466,352,366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="5.0">5</number>
only slightly concave on distal half, not as close to margin as in males; M bent anteriorly on distal third; CuA 
<number box="[430,438,391,405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
reaching wing margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,774,377,401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">Legs:</emphasis>
I: 
<number box="[807,845,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="2.4">2.4</number>
, 2.0, 
<number box="[908,946,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.2">1.2</number>
, 
<number box="[958,995,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number box="[1008,1046,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.4">0.4</number>
, 
<number box="[1058,1095,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.3">0.3</number>
, 
<number box="[1108,1146,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.3">0.3</number>
; II: 3.0, 
<number box="[1244,1281,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="2.5">2.5</number>
, 
<number box="[1294,1331,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.9">1.9</number>
, 
<number box="[1344,1382,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.9">0.9</number>
, 
<number box="[1394,1431,376,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.5">0.5</number>
, 
<number box="[151,188,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.3">0.3</number>
, 
<number box="[199,237,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.2">0.2</number>
; III: 
<number box="[291,328,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="2.9">2.9</number>
, 
<number box="[340,377,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="3.4">3.4</number>
, 1.0, 
<number box="[437,475,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.2">1.2</number>
, 
<number box="[485,523,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.6">0.6</number>
, 
<number box="[534,572,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.4">0.4</number>
, 
<number box="[583,621,415,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="0.3">0.3</number>
. Mostly dark yellow to pale brown. Cx II and III dark brown; trochanters pale brown; femora yellow to pale brown; tibia I pale brown, II and III yellow, base and tip of II and III infuscated; tarsi brown, base of II and III yellow. CxI covered by scattered black setulae anteriorly. Ventral surface of FII bare and scarcely infuscated. Tibia II: 
<number box="[531,545,523,547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
anterior seta near middle, 
<number box="[850,864,523,547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
posterodorsal seta at base, 
<number box="[1177,1191,523,547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
ventral setae at basal and apical 
<number box="[274,285,559,583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
/3, 1 anterodorsal, 
<number box="[501,515,559,583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
anteroventral and 
<number box="[728,742,559,583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
ventral setae at apex; tibia III: row of 
<number box="[1182,1224,559,583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
short dorsal setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,594,619]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">Abdomen:</emphasis>
T 
<number box="[304,345,595,619]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
with short vestiture of black setae dorsally, almost bare laterally. Sternites light brown, covered by few black setae, S 
<number box="[399,413,631,655]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="5.0">5</number>
darker. Oviscapt (
<figureCitation box="[627,737,631,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1026,1049]" captionTargetBox="[221,1402,188,1006]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1421,180,1024]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 9. Mberu pepocatu gen. nov. et sp. nov.: female oviscapt. 8, dorsal view. 9, left lateral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm. See Material and methods for explanation of abbreviations." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201979/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="41">
Figs. 
<number box="[694,737,631,655]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9</number>
</figureCitation>
) telescoped into pre-segments, T 
<number box="[1120,1147,631,655]" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" value="10.0">10</number>
flattened, prolonged and fused to cerci, acanthophorite dorsal with spines at apex.
</paragraph>
